  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\[\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}:\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}\\longrightarrow \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0817}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}})=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}},\\qquad\n\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}(x)\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.} Start with an unnormalized state or carrier value $z\\in \\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}$ and let the entry map act as\\[\nz_{0817}=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}(z).\n\\]\n\nNormalization divides the carrier by its global admissibility functional $Z_{0817}$:\\[\n\\widehat{z}_{0817}=\\frac{z_{0817}}{Z_{0817}},\\qquad Z_{0817}\\neq 0.\n\\]\n\nThe closure condition is the fixed-point law\\[\n\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}(\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}})=\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}},\\qquad \\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}(x)\\in\\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}}.\n\\]\n\nThus the Nonary derivation for [ID 0817] is the three-stage passage\n\\[\n\\mathcal{X}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{O}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{id0817}}\\xrightarrow{\\,\\mathcal{N}_{\\mathrm{TRAWIN}}\\,} \\mathcal{Y}_{\\mathrm{adm}},\n\\]\nwith the entry title fixing the meaning of the carrier and the TRAWIN normalization fixing the admissibility test.\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.} GLOBAL NORMALIZATION mathcalN supplies a sanity check for the Nonary chain: the entry is valid only when its output can be normalized without leaving the admissible class.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
